It is a secondary neuron of the 06B hemilineage (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It receives input in multiple regions and sends output to multiple regions (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is gaba (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 6 of these cells per organism and their somas are found in the metathoracic neuromere and prothoracic neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).
